<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10609&amp;p=119853#p119853"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />He's saying:<br />1- Scale up from 256x224 or 256x240 to 512x448 or 512x480, with sample-and-hold interpolation (&quot;nearest neighbor&quot;), such that each single pixel in the input produces four identical adjacent pixels in the output.<br />then<br />2- Scale this 512xY pixmap to 585xY (for NTSC) or 710xY (for PAL) using some fancier interpolation (linear, cubic)<br /><br />This way you get the sharpness of the pixels, without aliasing, and the correct aspect ratio.<br /></div><br /><br />Thnks!!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=72">Anes</a> — Fri Oct 25, 2013 5:19 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
