<author><name><![CDATA[mikejmoffitt]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-10-24T14:17:24-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-10-24T14:17:24-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10609&amp;p=119818#p119818</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10609&amp;p=119818#p119818"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Aspect Ratio and Direct3D 9]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10609&amp;p=119818#p119818"><![CDATA[
You will get pleasing results if you<br /><br />1) nearest-neighbor resize x 2 in both dimensions<br /><br />then<br /><br />2) scale to your target size with your filter of choice<br /><br />as this will preserve hard pixel edges much better for non-integer scaling values.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5314">mikejmoffitt</a> — Thu Oct 24, 2013 2:17 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
